<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   British Tourist Stabbed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2502143094 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 
25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2502143094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A responsible source at the Interior Ministry has 
said that in the wake of the criminal massacre that took place 
at dawn today at the Ibrahimi Mosque, some marches were staged 
in Amman to protest the heinous crime committed by Israeli 
settlers against pious worshipers in Hebron. 
  In a statement to the Jordanian News Agency, the source said 
Khalid Husni al-Qurashi attacked (Lon Edwards), a British 
tourist, at the Hashimite Square at noon today and stabbed him 
with a knife. The tourist was immediately rescued. He is now in 
a good condition. The assailant was arrested. 
  The Interior Ministry expresses its understanding of the 
overwhelming feelings that accompanied the grave event that took 
place at the Ibrahimi Mosque today. It, however, urges citizens 
to exercise self-restraint and close ranks so the feelings of 
support for our people in the occupied homeland will not turn 
into irresponsible, instantaneous reactions that harm our 
feelings and our just cause. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

