<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   President, Foreign Minister React to Hebron Killings </TI></H3>
<H4>   Mubarak Expresses `Deep Concern' </H4>
<F P=102> NC2502223794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2215 GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2502223794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 25 Feb (MENA)-- Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa 
has stated that President Muhammad Husni Mubarak has expressed 
his deep concern and condemnation of the horrible incidents that 
occurred at the Ibrahimi Mosque at dawn today. He said the 
president is following up on the details and developments, as 
well as the contacts made at the United Nations level and in the 
various world capitals. He added that the president gave 
instructions to support the convening of a UN Security Council 
meeting and stressed the need to take the necessary measures to 
protect the Palestinians and maintain their security. 
  The foreign minister added that the president telephoned 
Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat this evening and expressed 
his condolences over the martyrs of the painful incident. The 
president also consulted with 'Arafat on the steps to be taken. 
  President Mubarak received a message from U.S. President 
Bill 
Clinton and Israeli Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin, and expressed 
his deep concern at the threats to which the Palestinians are 
being subjected. During these contacts, the president stressed 
the need to take the necessary measures to avoid a recurrence of 
such an incident in the future, for preventing the settlers and 
extremists from threatening and terrifying the Palestinian 
citizens, and for taking this into consideration during the 
talks on the Palestinian-Israeli track, which basically aim to 
restore the rights of the Palestinian people, their land, and 
their security. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

