<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Bahrain </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry: Hebron Incident `Reprehensible' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2602152194 Manama WAKH in Arabic 1425 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN2602152194 </F>
<F P=104>  Manama WAKH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Manama, 26 Feb (WAKH) -- The State of Bahrain has 
strongly condemned and denounced the reprehensible crime and 
odious massacre the Zionist settlers have committed against 
Palestinian citizens who were performing dawn prayers at the 
Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron in the occupied West Bank, as a result 
of which scores were martyred and hundreds were wounded. 
  A responsible source at the Bahraini Ministry of Foreign 
Affairs has described this massacre as a terrorist act and held 
the Israeli Government and its security organs fully responsible 
for the terrorist acts these terrorist settlers carry out, which 
violate all international laws, norms, and charters and endanger 
the comprehensive, just, and lasting peace process in the region. 
  The source called on the international community and the UN 
Security Council, particularly its permanent members, to fully 
assume their responsibilities toward this act by not just 
denouncing and condemning it but by taking measures to protect 
the Palestinian people and secure their legitimate right to the 
establishment of their independent state on their national soil. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

