<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Reacts to Massacre at Hebron Mosque </TI></H3>
<H4>   Insists on UN Resolution </H4>
<F P=102> NC2702065394 London MBC Television in Arabic 2100 GMT 26 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2702065394 </F>
<F P=104>  London MBC Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with PLO Chairman Yasir 'Arafat by MBC Tunis </F>
correspondent Mufidah Hashani in Tunis on 26 February; recorded] 
  [Text] ['Arafat] The most important [word indistinct] is 
international protection for (?our people). We must see a 
solution for these settlements and the armed settlers, because 
they have proven to be time bombs liable to explode at any 
moment whether we pursue the negotiations or [words indistinct]. 
The situation may explode at any moment. They are time bombs. 
  [Hashani] What do you expect from the Security Council's 
meeting tonight? 
  ['Arafat] We are in continuous contact with the U.S. 
Administration on this issue because we insist on a resolution 
from the Security Council, not just a condemnation of [words 
indistinct]. 
  [Hashani] Where have the negotiations between you and the 
United States reached? 
  ['Arafat] They are continuing. 
  [Hashani] Any idea about the resolution expected to be 
passed? 
  ['Arafat, interrupting] [Words indistinct] but as I said, we 
are continuing our contacts with the U.S. Administration on this 
issue. 
  [Hashani] What about tomorrow's meeting with the Palestinian 
negotiators who were recalled by the PLO for a meeting in Tunis? 
Other than the settlements issue, can you clarify other topics 
of the meeting's agenda? 
  ['Arafat] I prefer not to talk too much and would rather 
like 
the deeds do the talking. There will be a complete and 
comprehensive assessment and afterward we will make a decision. 

</TEXT>

