<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Demonstrators Burn 'Arafat Effigy at Protest March </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2802160494 Paris AFP in English 1528 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2802160494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beirut, Feb 28 (AFP)--Around 3,000 angry pro-Iranian 
and pro-Syrian demonstrators burned an effigy of PLO chief Yasir 
'Arafat in a protest march here to mourn Palestinian Moslems 
gunned down in Hebron. 
  Hundreds of Palestinian women marched alongside the 
demonstrators carrying black flags in mourning for the 52 
Palestinian Moslems who were killed in a West Bank mosque on 
Friday by an Israeli settler. 
  They shouted "Death to 'Arafat" and "Death to Zionists" 
before burning an effigy of the PLO leader at the Martyrs 
Cemetery, where many Palestinians killed in confrontations with 
Israelis are buried alongside Lebanese. 
  Supporters of Hezbollah and radical Palestinian 
organisations 
based in Damascus participated in the demonstration which took 
off from outside a mosque in Beirut's mostly Shiite Moslem 
southern suburbs. 
  Many denounced the September 13 peace deal between the PLO 
and Israel. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

