<H3> <TI>   Radio Updates Casualties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2702110594 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1040 GMT 27 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2702110594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] According to the latest report on the massacre 
that occurred in the Sayyidat al-Najat church in Zuq Micha'il, 
there are 10 dead and approximately 40 injured. They have been 
taken to hospitals in the area. Papal Nuncio Pablo Puente 
inspected the bombed church a short while ago. Prime Minister 
Rafiq al-Hariri also inspected the church before proceeding to 
Bkirki, where he is now meeting with Maronite Patriarch Sfayr. 
[passage omitted] 
  Interior Minister Bisharah Mirhij is now visiting casualties 
in the Sayyidat Lubnan Hospital in Juniyah. In a telephone 
call a short while ago he affirmed to us that Lebanon is 
stronger than such incidents and will survive through its sons' 
unity and cohesion. He stressed that morale is high, that the 
Lebanese people will adhere to their basic principles, and that 
no event will disturb the general national security and peace. 
  He said that the casualties suffer from serious injuries but 
morale is high, particularly among the families of the victims, 
doctors, and nurses. He stressed that the security forces are 
continuing their investigations and that sappers had managed to 
defuse the explosive charges that were set to explode after the 
initial explosion, which occurred during mass. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

