<H3> <TI>   President, Others Comment on Church Bombing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Prime Minister Comments </H4>
<F P=102> NC2702150594 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1130 GMT 27 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2702150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [News conference by Prime Minister Rafiq al-Hariri with </F>
unidentified correspondents on 27 February; place not 
given--recorded] 
  [Text] [Al-Hariri] The most important thing is that the 
Lebanese should not be dragged into this plan that is clearly 
being supported by foreign hands. We are all one people, one 
hand. Whatever pains one area pains another area. God willing, 
we will transcend this ordeal and open our eyes so that no one 
will deceive us. 
  [Reporter] [Question indistinct]? 
  [Al-Hariri] It is clear [words indistinct] a Christian area 
in Kasrawan to cause sectarian strife. However, it is clear 
this will not affect the Lebanese. The Lebanese, Muslims and 
Christians, are one hand. 
  [Reporter] [Question indistinct]? 
  [Al-Hariri] The churches and mosques have their sanctity. 
During the worst days of the Lebanese war, no such thing 
happened. So it is clear that whoever did this thing wanted to 
inflict a deep wound. However, the Lebanese with their 
willpower and their faith in God and their homeland will not be 
dragged into such plans. 

</TEXT>

