<H3> <TI>   President, Others Comment on Church Bombing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Speaker Urges Vigilance </H4>
<F P=102> NC2702145894 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1135 GMT 27 Feb 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2702145894 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chamber of Deputies Speaker Nabih Birri has stated 
that the purpose of this abominable crime against worshipers in 
Sayyidat al-Najat Church was to sabotage general stability in 
Lebanon. He said this crime, which coincided with an Israeli 
escalation in southern Lebanon, is an attempt to divert world 
attention from the Ibrahimi Mosque massacre. He noted that 
Israel is behind all this. 
  Speaker Birri called on the Lebanese to be vigilant and 
responsible so that we will all emerge from this test with more 
faith in Lebanon. 

</TEXT>

