Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement by Maronite patriarch Butrus Sfayr in Zuq </F>
Mikha'il on 27 Feb-- recorded] 
  [Text] A massacre of this kind is indescribable because it 
is very painful. It targeted not only this church but peace 
itself not just in Lebanon but in the whole region. Therefore, 
we vehemently condemn this massacre and implore God to remove 
hatred and prejudice from people's hearts. The criminals should 
respect human lives that belong to God and not to them. Those 
who perpetrated this act have lost a great part of their 
humanity. We invoke God to instill peace in people's hearts in 
this homeland and in the region. 

