<F P=100> Inter-Arab Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   League Head Asks Libya To `Reconsider' Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2802163794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1226 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2802163794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tripoli, 28 Feb (MENA)--Arab League Secretary 
General Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid has held an urgent telephone 
conversation with Colonel al-Qadhdhafi, in which he called on 
the Libyan leader to reconsider Libya's decision to withdraw 
from the Arab League and not to present the decision to the 
Basic People's Congresses until a meeting is arranged between 
Libyan officials and the Arab League chief. 
  Jum'ah al-Fazzani, secretary of Libya's People's General 
Committee for Unity, arrived in Cairo yesterday and told Dr. 
'Abd-al-Majid that the Secretariat of the People's General 
Committee for Unity (Ministry of Unity) is about to present a 
draft resolution to the Basic People's Congresses, calling for 
Libya's withdrawal from the Arab League on the grounds that the 
League failed to provide any service to the Arab people. 
  [Cairo MENA in Arabic at 1323 GMT on 28 February, in a 
Tripoli-datelined item, adds: "Counselor Tal'at Hamid, press 
adviser to the secretary general of the Arab League, today said 
that Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid has not received a message from Jum'ah 
al-Fazzani, secretary of the Libyan Unity Committee, containing 
Libya's request to withdraw from the Arab League. Hamid added 
that Dr. 'Abd-al-Majid has not sent any message dealing with 
this topic to Libyan leader Col. Mu'ammar al-Qadhdhafi."] 

</TEXT>

