<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hijackers Take Over Air-Algerie Airliner </TI></H3>
<H4>   Hijackers Surrender in Spain </H4>
<F P=102> LD2802201494 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpts] There was a happy ending this evening to today's 
hijacking of the Air Algerie Boeing-727 to Spain, following the 
surrender of the three hijackers to the Spanish authorities and 
the release of all passengers. [passage omitted] 
  The hijackers made contact with the Spanish authorities and 
later released 12 passengers, including 8 women, 2 men, and 2 
children. According to the Spanish minister of transport, the 
hijackers asked for political asylum. 
  Permanent contacts were established between the Algerian 
Embassy in Spain, represented by the Consul-general, and the 
Spanish authorities in Alicante. Immediately after the plane 
was hijacked, the Algerian Foreign Ministry set up an emergency 
committee to follow up developments of the affair and take the 
necessary measures. The hijacking, which saw a happy ending, 
lasted only a few hours and is now over. 

</TEXT>

