<F P=102>  BK2602161894 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1530 
GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2602161894 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] India has strongly condemned yesterday's massacre of 
nearly 50 Palestinian worshipers in the West Bank town of Hebron 
by an Israeli gunman. New Delhi also conveyed its condolences 
to the members of the bereaved families. An External Affairs 
Ministry spokesman said today that India calls upon Israel to 
take immediate and effective steps to ensure that such incidents 
are not repeated. Israel has also been urged to bring the 
culprits to book and protect the lives and properties of 
innocent people in the occupied territory. New Delhi expressed 
the hope that all concerned will adopt a path of restraint in 
bringing down tension and will not vitiate the climate of peace 
and tranquillity to make the West Asia peace process a success. 

