<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Bhutto Expresses `Anguish' Over Hebron Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2602103894 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0100 
GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2602103894 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Ms. Benazir Bhutto has expressed 
deep sorrow and anguish over the unprovoked and brutal assault 
on the congregation of Muslims inside the Ibrahim Mosque at 
al-Khalil city, in which more than 50 Muslims were martyred and 
several others injured. While condemning the dastardly and 
despicable act on behalf of the government and the people of 
Pakistan, the prime minister in a statement issued in Islamabad 
last night, said the incident reflects religious intolerance 
which nowadays has been directed toward the Muslims of 
Palestine, Bosnia, and Kashmir. While condemning this tendency 
toward religious intolerance, she said Pakistan considers it as 
nothing but unreasonable steps taken at individual and 
collective levels. Pakistan has taken note of PLO Chairman 
Yasir 'Arafat's appeal to convene an emergency session of the UN 
Security Council and as a member of this body, Pakistan will 
give full attention to this serious matter. The prime minister 
urged the members of the UN Security Council to make use of the 
tenets enshrined in the UN Charter and to implement the UN 
Security Council Resolution Number 242 and 338, and other 
resolutions on Jerusalem. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

