<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senate `Strongly' Condemns Hebron Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  BK2702113394 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 1000 
GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2702113394 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Urdu </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In Islamabad today, the Senate unanimously adopted a 
resolution strongly condemning the incident of firing at Ibrahim 
Mosque in al-Khalil City. Scores of people were martyred or 
injured in the firing by a Zionist with the help of Israeli 
authorities. In the resolution presented by Justice Minister 
Iqbal Haider and Hafiz Hussain Ahmad, the house described the 
incident as the century's worst act of terrorism. The house 
also decided to dispatch copies of the resolution to various 
international fora. 
  In her brief speech on the occasion, Prime Minister Benazir 
Bhutto, on behalf of the government and the people of Pakistan, 
expressed deep sympathy with the bereaved families. Expressing 
complete solidarity of the people of Pakistan with the 
Palestinian people, she said Pakistan will continue to extend 
full support to the cause of the Palestinians forever. 

