<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Majid Reportedly Moved From Amman After Surgery </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2502154994 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 25 Feb 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> PM2502154994 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "A Hospital Is Sought To Treat Husayn </F>
Kamil"] 
  [Text] Amman, AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT -- Iraqi sources have 
confirmed that Husayn Kamil Hasan al-Majid, the Iraqi 
president's son-in-law [and industry minister], has been moved 
from Jordan with a view to giving him intensive treatment after 
the first brain surgery he underwent 10 days ago. The sources 
believe al-Majid may end up in a Swiss hospital, as the French 
authorities refused to grant him an entry visa to their 
territory. The Iraqi Embassy in Amman sought to move the Iraqi 
president's son-in-law to Switzerland, Cuba, Romania, or Russia. 

</TEXT>

