<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Northern, Southern Forces Reportedly Clash </TI></H3>
<H4>   Update on Clashes, Military Moves </H4>
<F P=102> PM2502220394 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 25 Feb 94 pp1, 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM2502220394 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Reports by 'Abd-al-Rahman al-Haydari and Faysal Karam in </F>
Sanaa and Iqbal 'Ali 'Abdallah in Aden] 
  [Excerpts] The situation remained tense yesterday in 
Yemen's Abyan Governorate as the General People's Congress [GPC] 
and the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] exchanged accusations about 
provocative military movements. [passage omitted] 
  Military sources in Sanaa have revealed that a number of 
soldiers from the northern al-'Amaliqah Brigade were ambushed 
yesterday morning in the town of Zinjibar, capital of the Abyan 
Governorate, by soldiers from the al-Wahdah Brigade and some YSP 
militia. They said that "a limited number of al-'Amaliqah 
Brigade soldiers were on their way to al-Razi Hospital in the 
town of Ja'ar to collect the body of a colleague of theirs 
treacherously killed by soldiers from the Madram Brigade camp, 
when they were intercepted and fired on by an armed group in 
front of the hospital. Brigade member Hazzam 'Ali Musayli was 
wounded." 
  According to other reports, tanks and howitzer artillery 
units from the YSP's al-'Anad camp have moved in the direction 
of the areas of al-Milah, al-Hubaylayn, and al-Dali' in the 
province of Lahij "to occupy the old partition positions and 
prepare to besiege the forces of the (northern) 2nd armored 
brigade stationed in the area of al-Milah in Lahij." 
  "Informed sources" in Aden have been quoted as saying that 
at 
dawn yesterday 12 tanks tightened their siege of the central 
security battalion in the Radfan camp in al-Sawlaban (Aden). 
They added that "the supply of water and electricity to the 
battlion were still cut off on the direct orders of Aden 
Governor Brigadier General Salih Munsir al-Suyayli who ordered 
the expulsion of that battalion from Aden to the remote area of 
Dar Sa'd." [passage omitted] 
  According to reports received in Aden from the Abyan 
Governorate, forces of the southern al-Wahdah Brigade "continue 
to hunt down members of the Islamic Jihad Organization 
concentrated in the al-Maraqishah mountains in the directorate 
of Mudiyah." 
  The same reports revealed "the arrest of 85 Islamic Jihad 
members of various Arab nationalities who participated in the 
armed clashes in the directorate" since last Monday between 
forces of the northern al-'Amaliqah Brigade and forces of the 
southern al-Wahdah Brigade which came from Hadramaut (some 920 
km east of Aden). [passage omitted] 
  AL-HAYAH learned from YSP sources yesterday that the YSP's 
Political Bureau has been in "continuous session" since 'Ali 
Salim al-Bid's return to Aden the day before yesterday after 
brief visits to Saudi Arabia, the Sultanate of Oman, and Eritrea 
after signing the Pledge and Accord Document in the Jordanian 
capital last Sunday. The sources said that "al-Bid returned 
secretly to Aden after the discovery that there was going to be 
yet another attempt by the air defenses of the al-'Amaliqah 
Brigade to target his plane as it crossed the Abyan air space." 
  They also said that shots were fired by al-'Amaliqah forces 
on an Ethiopian Airlines plane over Abyan as it was on a regular 
weekly flight to Aden International Airport on the morning of 
the day before yesterday but it was not hit. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

