<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Northern, Southern Forces Reportedly Clash </TI></H3>
<H4>   Units Ordered to Precrisis Posts </H4>
<F P=102> NC2802100294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 0920 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2802100294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Aden, 28 Feb (MENA)-- The military situation and 
developments in Yemen were discussed in Aden yesterday evening 
by a joint military committee in the presence of Defense 
Minister Staff Brigadier General Haytham Qasim Tahir. 
  During the meeting, the committee expressed the hope that 
efforts will succeed in putting all the remaining tense areas 
under control, returning all military units to pre-crisis 
positions, and showing these units' commitment to the 
committee's instructions in accordance with the authority 
entrusted to it by Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and 
Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid. 
  The committee's official spokesman announced that the 
committee-- composed of the Yemeni-Omani-Jordanian 
commission--has met in Sanaa and Aden in the presence of the 
U.S. and French military attaches. It agreed to return all the 
units that had left their posts during the crisis to their 
original stations, stop the clashes that have occurred in 
certain areas, prevent the setting up of new posts on public 
roads, and remove those newly set up posts, and prohibit any 
military movement unless the Joint Military Committee approves 
it. 
  The spokesman stated that the committee will undertake 
observation duties and supervise the implementation of its 
decision as of today, Monday. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

