<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Northern, Southern Forces Reportedly Clash </TI></H3>
<H4>   Defense Ministry: Attacks Launched in South </H4>
<F P=102> EA2802203094 Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1800 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> EA2802203094 </F>
<F P=104>  Aden Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by the Office of the Defense Minister; </F>
place and date not given] 
  [Text] Less than 24 hours after the signing by the 
president and the vice president of the document giving a 
mandate to the joint military committee to tackle the 
deterioration of the military and security situation and the 
implementation of the security and military aspects of the 
pledge and accord document, we were surprised by the 
irresponsible behavior on the part of the giants' [al-'Amaliqah] 
forces. This behavior was represented by their attack on the 
36th Infantry Battalion of the Unity [al-Wahdah] Brigade 
stationed in Mudiyah Province in Abyan Governorate. The 
al-'Amaliqah forces used in their barbarous attack Katyusha 
missile launchers, tanks and artillery, as well as other medium 
and light weapons. This attack targeting the 36th Battalion was 
accompanied by another military attack, targeting towns, 
villages and small villages in Mudiyah Province, when military 
units of the al-'Amaliqah forces carried out intensive shelling 
of peaceful inhabitants. 

</TEXT>

