<H3> <TI>   Salih, al-Bid Sign Military Committee Document </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2802063494 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 0500 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2802063494 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih and Vice 
President 'Ali Salim al-Bid yesterday evening signed a document 
on setting up the military committee in charge of withdrawing 
military units and returning them to their barracks and 
following up the implementation of the provisions of the Pledge 
and Agreement document. 
  In another development, the European Union ambassadors in 
Sanaa appealed to all the parties to the recent violent clashes 
to refrain from making any military moves that could adversely 
affect the implementation of the Yemeni reconciliation agreement. 

</TEXT>

