<H4>   Sanctions Against Israel Urged </H4>
<F P=102> LD2602215394 Tripoli Libyan Television Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 26 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2602215394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tripoli Libyan Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The secretary of the General People's Committee for 
Foreign Liaison and International Cooperation has summoned the 
ambassadors of the UN Security Council permanent members, 
accredited in the Great Jamahiriyah; he told them of the Great 
Jamahiriyah's outrage at the wanton massacre carried out by the 
Zionist occupiers inside the al-Ibrahimi holy shrine against 
worshippers, the sons of the Palestinian Arab people. 
  The brother secretary of the General People's Committee for 
Foreign Liaison and International Cooperation has asserted the 
need for the UN Security Council to impose harsh sanctions on 
the Zionist entity, not furnish it with any weapons and to 
impose a blockade against it. 
  He stressed, moreover, that if the Council failed to take 
any 
of the abovementioned measures, such a failure would be seen an 
encouragement for the Israelis to perpetrate further massacres 
and annihilate the Palestinian Arab people. 
  The brother secretary has asked the ambassadors to convey 
the 
abovementioned protest to their respective governments. 

