<H3> <TI>   Assistant Foreign Minister Meets Israeli Envoy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2702122794 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1210 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2702122794 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 27 Feb (MENA)--Assistant Foreign Minister 
Badr Hammam today met with David Sultan, Israel's ambassador in 
Cairo. 
  The Israeli ambassador stated after the meeting that they 
had 
discussed the attack on Palestinian worshipers at the 
al-Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron. 
  He said that the Israeli Government is trying to take 
measures to prevent a repetition of such incidents. 
  He added that the march to peace must not stop, because if 
it 
does that would mean that the extremists have succeeded in 
achieving their goals. 
  In this regard, he affirmed the importance of resuming the 
peace march as quickly as possible so that the extremists do not 
reach their objectives. 

</TEXT>

