Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 28 Feb (MENA)--The Muslim Brotherhood group, 
whose activities are banned in Egypt, has issued a statement 
denouncing the bombing of a church in Kasrawan, Lebanon. The 
statement also denounces the criminal hands which terrorize the 
public and stab Muslims in their backs as they kneel down to 
pray. 
  The statement says that enemies are hatching conspiracies to 
fan the flames of sedition among our people. We should foil 
these conspiracies through the unity of our ranks and the 
mobilization of our potential, the statement adds. 

