<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Police Kill 5 `Terrorists' in Aswan Sweep </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2802144294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1300 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC2802144294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Aswan, 28 Feb (MENA)--Security forces killed five 
terrorists today following a chase through farm areas in Aswan. 
  The incident took place during sweeps that began last night 
in Aswan. Security organs killed three wanted terrorists last 
night after they attacked a policeman. 
  According to security sources, the dead men were dangerous 
terrorists wanted by the police in connection with several 
crimes. 
  The eight terrorists attacked the sentry at the license 
office in Idfu yesterday evening, captured his rifle, and fled 
in a minitruck toward the village of (Kalj al-Jabal). The 
security forces immediately chased them and managed to kill 
three of them. The remaining terrorists hid in a sugar cane 
plantation. A police force led by Major General Sami 
'Abd-al-Jawad, assistant to the interior minister and director 
of the Security Department in Aswan, surrounded them and 
exchanged fire. As day broke today, the police force raided the 
sugar cane plantation and found the bodies of the five other 
terrorists, the sentry's stolen rifle, and some weapons and 
ammunition. During the manhunt and raid, two policemen were 
martyred and another was injured and taken to the central 
hospital in Idfu. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

