<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Executive Committee Meeting Resumes in Tunis </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802155694 Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1500 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802155694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tunis Tunisian Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The discussions of the PLO Executive Committee have 
resumed today at the PLO headquarters in Tunis in anticipation 
of a firm resolution from the UN Security Council following the 
massacre at the Ibrahimi mosque in Hebron. 
  Within this context the PLO leaders are expecting the UN 
Security Council to issue a resolution that will guarantee the 
effective protection of the Palestinians in the occupied 
territories before the final answer is announced to President 
Bill Clinton's request that the negotiations should be resumed 
in Washington. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

