<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin Briefs Ambassadors on Hebron Mosque Attack </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2602191594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 26 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2602191594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin says the talks with 
the Palestinians will resume in Washington on 2 March upon the 
invitation of President Clinton. Israel accepted the 
President's invitation, but it is still not clear whether the 
Palestinians also accepted. The prime minister made these 
remarks to 70 ambassadors posted in Israel whom he summoned to 
his office in Tel Aviv in order to brief them about the Hebron 
incidents and the political situation. 
  The prime minister called on the Palestinians to act like 
Israel and to totally separate between the Hebron incident and 
the continuation of the political process. Our correspondent 
Sheli Yehimovich reports the prime minister reiterated that as 
an Israeli, a Jew, and a human being, he is ashamed that an 
Israeli Jew perpetrated this massacre. He emphasized, however, 
that there is no proof that it was part of an organized action. 

</TEXT>

