<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rabin `Knows' Peace Negotiations To Be Resumed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0103053394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 0500 GMT 1 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0103053394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin says he hopes and 
knows that the peace negotiations will be resumed. Speaking to 
the Conference of Presidents of Major American Jewish 
Organizations, he said the massacre at the mosque in Hebron 
would be remembered as the Black Friday of the Jewish people. 
Rabin was asked if he would accept the PLO's demand for an 
international force in the territories to protect the 
Palestinians: 
  [Begin Rabin recording] In the DOP [Declaration of 
Principles], it is written international presence but not 
international forces presence, and we offer that in the context 
of the Gaza-Jericho First, we will not oppose representatives or 
international presence of certain individuals in Gaza and 
Jericho -- not a force, not armed people. This is part of the 
DOP. Whatever we sign, we'll stick to it. All the other 
demands I believe that you mentioned -- dismantling of 
settlements, no; disarm of all arms from settlers, no. [end 
recording] 

</TEXT>

