<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Arrangement for Compensation to Victims Concluded </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0103093194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0900 GMT 1 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0103093194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] According to the arrangement concluded between the 
Finance and the Labor and Social Welfare Ministries regarding 
compensation to the families of the Hebron massacre victims, the 
total amount of funds to be paid will amount to dozens of 
millions of shekels. This is reported by our correspondent 
Ya'el Ayalon. The payment will be a one-time compensation to the 
families of the dead and the wounded. During the first stage, 
each family who lost one of its members will receive an advance 
payment of 5,000 shekels. Ora Namir, labor and social welfare 
minister, says this is a humanitarian step. National Insurance 
Institute Chairman Yosi Tamir notes that this move is not 
intended to set a precedent. 

</TEXT>

