<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   IDF Kills Arab Youth During Riot in Gaza </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2702120594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 27 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2702120594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] In a massive riot in the al-Zaytun neighborhood 
of Gaza, a 17-year-old Palestinian was killed. Our 
correspondent Moti Amir reports that he was shot by soldiers, 
who also injured 20 other Palestinians. They were taken for 
treatment in local hospitals. 
  In the Jordan Rift Valley, the hunt continues for the 
terrorist who this morning entered a hothouse in Gitit and fired 
at one of the workers, but caused no damage. In Rafah, a youth 
was badly injured by soldiers after he threw rocks at them. 
  In the Bedouin village of Tel Sheva' in the Negev, 10 people 
were injured in a violent clash between the police and 
demonstrators protesting the Hebron killings. Our correspondent 
Nisim Qeynan reports that the police detained six of the 
demonstrators. The policemen were pelted with rocks and had to 
use tear gas to disperse the demonstrating Bedouin. Riots also 
took place in the villages of Kusayfah, 'Aro'er, and Laggiyah. 
  In al-Tirah in the triangle, a police officer was stabbed in 
the back a short while ago. Our correspondent Yafa Glick 
reports that he was taken to the Me'ir Hospital. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

