<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Two Arabs Killed, 17 Wounded in Territories </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2802162694 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 28 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2802162694 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Two Arabs were killed in the territories today in 
clashes with IDF [Israel Defense Forces] soldiers, one in 
Nabulus and another in Hebron. Another 17 Arabs were wounded: 
three were seriously wounded in Nabulus, one was moderately 
injured in the village of Tuqu', and 13 were wounded in the Gaza 
Strip. 
  Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that a riot occurred 
near 
the Cave of the Patriarchs, and an IDF soldier was lightly 
wounded by a stone. 
  Disturbances continue in East Jerusalem, particularly in 
Shu'fat and in Al-Tur. Our police affairs correspondent Aviv 
Bushinsky reports that the rioters set tires on fire and threw 
stones at Border Police units. In East Jerusalem's central bus 
station, a burning object was thrown at an empty bus and the 
driver's seat was lightly damaged. 
  Some 1,500 people marched in Haifa for the second day in a 
mourning procession over the massacre in Hebron. They marched 
from Wadi Nisnas to the municipality building. One of the 
speakers was Haifa Mayor 'Amram Mitzna'. Our correspondent Nati 
Zilberman reports that a stone was thrown at a police patrol car 
during the procession, but nobody was hurt. A 14-year-old boy 
who threw the stone was detained for questioning. 

</TEXT>

