<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Rioting Additional Arrests, Casualties </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2802202094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1800 GMT 28 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2802202094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Dani Gur-Arye] </F>
  [Excerpts] Once again today, Palestinians clashed with 
Israeli troops on both sides of the Green Line. Once again, 
casualties and arrests. 
  In the territories residents defied the curfew in effect 
almost everywhere in the West Bank and Gaza, blocking roads, 
burning tires, and throwing stones. The most severe incident 
took place in Salfit, near Tulkarm, where some 60 residents 
surrounded an Army outpost, showering it with stones, bottles, 
and petrol bombs. Soldiers emerged on foot to disperse the 
demonstrators. They opened fire when one of the youths 
brandished a knife. Five demonstrators were wounded, two 
seriously. [passage omitted] 
  More troubling for the authorities are the ongoing 
demonstrations in Arab communities within the Green Line. The 
focus of the unrest shifted to Galilee today, where some 50 
Israeli Arabs were arrested. In Nazareth youths blocked the main 
road and threw stones at the bank, the post office, and 
government offices. Police initially refrained from entering 
the city in large numbers, but moved in early in the afternoon 
to break up the demonstrations. Thirty three people were 
arrested in the city. There were also large demonstrations in 
Kafr Kana and Baqa al-Gharbiyah. 
  In East Jerusalem, two policemen and eight Palestinians were 
wounded in clashes today. 
  [Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew at 1900 GMT on 28 February 
adds that "a Molotov cocktail was thrown at an Israeli car at 
the Armon Hanetziv neighborhood this evening. The car was not 
damaged. A rented car was set on fire at Wadi al-Jawz in East 
Jerusalem, and a Molotov cocktail was thrown at a Border Police 
vehicle in the Old City of Jerusalem, but the vehicle was not 
damaged. There were no casualties in these three incidents. 
  ["In the center of Hebron, several shots were directed at an 
IDF [Israel Defense Forces] patrol not far from Gross Square. 
There were no casualties. The patrol soldiers returned fire 
and began searches." 
  [Also, "six masked people were caught in the village of 
Abu-Dis in East Jerusalem; two youths who threw Molotov 
cocktails at the security forces in Khan Yunus were detained; 
and five youths who were on their way to committing arson were 
caught at Wadi al-Jawz in East Jerusalem."] 

</TEXT>

