<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Settlement Council To Review `Attitude' Toward Kakh </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2802204994 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 28 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA2802204994 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Council of Jewish Settlements in Judaea, 
Samaria, and Gaza which convened today to discuss the security 
situation has announced its objection to the expressions of joy 
over the murder in Hebron. This is included in a series of 
decisions adopted by the heads of the council during their 
meeting. Our correspondent Ya'el Ayalon reports that it was 
further decided that in the future the council will hold an 
extensive discussion about the attitude toward the Kakh 
movement. The council has also decided to launch an information 
campaign within the settlements so as to curb the activities of 
Kakh members. The first in a series of decisions made by the 
council expresses deep sorrow and shock about the murder in 
Hebron. The council heads also categorically condemn any harm 
inflicted on innocent people, share in the grief of the victims' 
families, and repudiate the expressions of joy regarding the 
murder. 
  The other decisions adopted by the council takes a negative 
view of the measures the government adopted yesterday. 

</TEXT>

