<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials, Commentaries React to Hebron Massacre </TI></H3>
<H4>   Yazdi Condemns `Savage Attack' </H4>
<F P=102> LD2802163694 Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network in 
Persian 1530 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2802163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRIB Television First Program Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] At today's session of the judicial authorities, 
which was chaired by Ayatollah Yazdi, the head of the judiciary, 
Mr. Yazdi condemned the Zionists' savage attack at the Friday 
prayers services in al-Khalil. He said: The negligence of the 
advocates of human rights and international organizations, 
including the United Nations, in such cases, and the lack of 
prompt practical deterrent measures cause public opinion to 
doubt the sincerity of those organizations. 
  He added: This situation is such that there is a need to 
form 
a powerful international criminal court, higher than The Hague 
Court of Justice -- to realize rights, carry out justice, and 
punish offenders. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

