<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israeli President Extends Condolences to Mubarak </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2702132194 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1230 GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2702132194 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Israeli President Ezer Weizman telephoned President 
Husni Mubarak this afternoon to express his country's 
denunciation of the horrible crime that took place at the Hebron 
Mosque. He also extended condolences to President Mubarak 
regarding the Palestinian victims. He informed President 
Mubarak that he had visited Hebron this morning to meet with its 
mayor, the city mufti, and senior officials to extend 
condolences for the victims of the abominable crime. 

