<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further Reports on Zuq Mikha'il Church Bombing </TI></H3>
<H4>   Al-Hirawi Addresses Funeral of Victims </H4>
<F P=102> NC2802114694 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1015 GMT 28 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2802114694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Zuq Mikha'il has bid a last farewell to its victims 
in a mass funeral held at the Sayyidat al-Najat Church in that 
town. The holy communion was chaired by Maronite Patriarch Mar 
Nasrallah Butrus Sfayr, assisted by a group of patriarchs and 
priests. President Ilyas al-Hirawi and his wife attended the 
mass. The prime minister was represented by Minister Hagop 
Demerdjian and Chamber of Deputies Speaker Nabih Birri was 
represented by Deputy Rashid al-Khazin. A large number of 
ministers, deputies, and key figures also attended. 
  In his homily, Patriarch Sfayr said: Some say that such 
crimes happen in the best of countries, but this is not 
satisfactory. There they capture the culprits, who then receive 
the punishment they deserve. Here however, the perpetrators 
remain unknown, either due to impotence or willingness to keep 
people in the dark; both amount to the same thing. These two 
reasons do not exempt the state from its responsibility for 
finding the culprits; they do not alleviate the obsessions and 
fears; and they do not insure safety for citizens. The Maronite 
patriarch urged a state that applies right and justice and 
treats all equally. 
  President al-Hirawi said in a speech: I came to this church 
to accept condolences in the name of the whole country, and to 
say that for thousands of years we have been destined to stand 
fast, from Wadi Qannubin to the cedar-clad mountains, to any 
spot in this sacred land. He added: I came to this church to 
say, in front of Your Beatitude, the other priests, and the 
representative of the Pope that we will remain faithful to this 
pledge, standing fast in Lebanon. 
  [(Clandestine) Radio Free Lebanon in Arabic at 1010 GMT on 
28 
February adds: "President al-Hirawi said: We will remain 
faithful to the pledge, and the hands that encroach upon Lebanon 
will be cut off. Tendentious people have no place among us. 
When peace began its march, they began their shameful acts."] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

