<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ghawshah Links Resuming Talks to Israeli Measures </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0203131194 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Arabic 1044 GMT 2 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0203131194 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with PLO Executive Committee member Samir </F>
Ghawshah, by Sa'id Mu'addi, place and date not given; from the 
"With the Midday Events" program -- recorded] 
  [Text] [Mu'addi] Dr. Samir Ghawshah, member of the PLO 
Executive Committee: The PLO leadership is continuing its 
consultations with all parties. Does this mean this decision 
will be crucial and decisive for the peace process? 
  [Ghawshah] The PLO leadership is continuing its contacts on 
all levels and in more than one area, whether on the Arab or 
international levels. In the meantime, the PLO leadership is 
pursuing political activity on all levels. We would like to say 
that the support extended to us and the denunciation and 
condemnation of the massacre perpetrated against our people in 
Hebron are indications that the world understands and 
sympathizes with the just Palestinian demands. Moreover, we 
believe that much of the future of the political process hinges 
upon the positions to be adopted by Mr. Rabin and his government 
and on the measures and positions that will be taken toward the 
Palestinian demands for the sake of advancing the peace process 
and extricating it from the vicious circle. I think the 
experience of the past months clearly showed that it was the 
Palestinian side which was serious in its quest for peace, 
termination of all acts of violence, withdrawal, and coexistence 
for all peoples in the region. 
  [Mu'addi] Dr. Samir, the peace cosponsors--Russia and the 
United States--are mediating an end to the causes which stopped 
the peace talks. Yesterday, a Russian envoy met with Yasir 
'Arafat and will meet today with the decisionmakers in Israel. 
What conditions has the PLO conveyed to the Russian envoy? 
  [Ghawshah] During yesterday's meeting, the Russian envoy and 
brother Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] discussed in detail the peace 
process and the obstacles facing it, especially the recent 
developments. The most important point of discussion was the 
need to provide protection and security for our people, 
especially after it has been proven that the Israeli Army did 
not and will not carry out its duty in preventing attacks on our 
people. The two sides discussed the obstacles facing the peace 
process and Israel's failure to carry out its commitments as 
stated in the Declaration of Principles. These included its 
delay of withdrawal from the Jericho and Gaza areas, earlier 
scheduled for 13 December. The entire peace process was 
discussed. A basic Palestinian demand was submitted; namely, 
the need to provide protection and security for the Palestinian 
people and international observers to guarantee this security. 
  [Mu'addi] Dr. Samir, when do you expect the 
Israeli-Palestinian talks to resume and what about the 
Palestinian delegation which will leave for Washington? 
  [Ghawshah] The matter depends primarily on the measures and 
policies to be adopted by Mr. Rabin and his government. This is 
the issue. The first fact which should be considered is the 
degree of seriousness in taking measures and responding to the 
Palestinian people's just demands. This is the first basic 
factor. The second is the extent to which the cosponsors of the 
political process will play their role and give a new push to 
the peace process. 
  [Mu'addi] Dr. Samir Ghawshah, member of the PLO Executive 
Committee. Thank you very much. 
  [Ghawshah] Thank you. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

