<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sha'th Meets Musa, Says `Impossible' To Resume Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0203122894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1140 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0203122894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 2 Mar (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa 
today met Dr. Nabil Sha'th, the head of the Palestinian 
delegation to the Taba talks. The meeting was attended by Sa'id 
Kamal, the Palestinian ambassador in Cairo. 
  Afterward, Dr. Sha'th said he gave Minister Musa a message 
from the Palestinian leadership to President Husni Mubarak. He 
said the message deals with developments following the 
abominable and criminal massacre committed by Israeli settlers 
with the support and backing of Israeli army units in the 
Ibrahimi Mosque in Hebron, developments to come in relation with 
this issue, and the Palestinian leadership's insistence on 
providing security for the Palestinian people under occupation 
until the Israeli withdrawal is effected according to the peace 
agreements. Sha'th added that it is impossible now to proceed 
with the negotiations with the Israelis without clear-cut and 
effective measures to disarm the settlers, secure international 
protection, and reconsider the settlement issue. He noted that 
this is an important issue without which it is difficult to 
build a real base for progress in the talks, as the Americans 
demand. 

</TEXT>

