<H3> <TI>   'Arafat, Christopher Discuss Aftermath of Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0103225094 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 2200 GMT 1 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0103225094 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The brother President Yasir 'Arafat received at 
midday today a telephone call from U.S. Secretary of State 
Warren Christopher. The latest developments regarding the 
Ibrahimi mosque massacre were discussed during the telephone 
conversation. The brother president stressed the need for the 
UN Security Council to issue a resolution that guarantees the 
safety and security of Palestinian citizens in the occupied 
Palestinian territories, including Holy Jerusalem, and 
entrusting an international force with this task. 

