<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Receives Envoy, Message From Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0103221894 Cairo MENA in Arabic 2140 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0103221894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tunis, 1 Mar (MENA)--The Palestinian news agency 
WAFA reported tonight that Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat 
received a written message from Russian President Boris Yeltsin. 
  The agency said that 'Arafat received this message when he 
met this evening with Mr. Igor Ivanov, Russian President 
Yeltsin's envoy, and that 'Arafat and Ivanov held extended and 
detailed talks on the current stage of the Middle East peace 
process after the al-Ibrahimi Mosque massacre in Hebron. They 
discussed the results of that massacre when all Arab parties to 
the talks suspended negotiations with Israel. 
  The news agency said that during his meeting, 'Arafat 
concentrated on the basic Palestinian demands at this stage, 
which are: 
  First, sending an international or multinational force to 
the 
occupied Palestinian territories, the West Bank and Gaza Strip, 
by coordinating and consulting with the co-sponsors of the peace 
process, the United States and Russia, and the UN secretary 
general to guarantee the security and safety of the Palestinian 
people there. 
  Second, disarming the settlers and preserving public peace. 
  Third, starting to dismantle the settlements that have 
extremists in them. 

</TEXT>

