<H3> <TI>   Fatah Hawks Urge 'Arafat To Halt Peace Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0203081594 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0203081594 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The pursued Fatah hawks strugglers inside and 
outside the occupied territories have issued a statement saying: 
The heinous crime and the dastardly massacre perpetrated 
against our people's sons at the Ibrahimi Mosque, a house of 
God, in the blessed month of Ramadan is cogent proof of the 
impossibility of peace or coexistence with the enemies of God 
and mankind. 
  The statement added: We, the pursued Fatah hawks inside and 
outside the occupied territories, demand that the 'Arafat 
leadership halt its negotiations with the Zionist enemy. 
Similarly, we demand all fighting Palestinian factions to unify 
themselves in the crucible of the revolution and armed struggle 
against enemy troops and the hordes of settlers, who are engaged 
in murder and terrorism against our Palestinian people, who are 
fighting the Zionist injustice and repression. 
  Concluding their statement, the Fatah hawks said: Our 
people's dignity cannot be safeguarded unless we extricate our 
national rights by force, just as they have been usurped by 
force. 

</TEXT>

