<H3> <TI>   Hamas Welcomes Suspension, Denounces 'Arafat Stand </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0103205994 (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio in 
Arabic 1730 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0103205994 </F>
<F P=104>  (Clandestine) Al-Quds Palestinian Arab Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Islamic Resistance Movement, Hamas, has issued 
a statement declaring the decision of Jordan, Syria, and Lebanon 
to suspend the ongoing negotiations in protest against the ugly 
massacre of innocent worshipers at the holy Ibrahimi Mosque a 
good step. 
  Hamas denounced the shaky, hesitant position of Yasir 
'Arafat 
as a submissive position that does not take into consideration 
the Palestinian blood that has been spilled or the anger of the 
Palestinian people everywhere. 
  The statement further said: We think that 'Arafat's stands 
serve the interests of the Zionist enemy, which seeks to placate 
popular rage over the massacre. 
  The statement added: We consider insistence on pursuing a 
policy of relinquishment and continuing the negotiations, rather 
than responding to an overwhelming popular desire to withdraw 
from the talks, as treason against our people. 
  An official Hamas spokesman said that it is a priority of 
the 
popular forces to maintain a strong popular momentum inside the 
territories and in the diaspora and to remain determined to 
achieve their goals. 

</TEXT>

