<H3> <TI>   PFLP Leader Urges Integrated Action Plan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0103131794 Amman AL-BILAD in Arabic 1 Mar 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> JN0103131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-BILAD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with George Habash, secretary general of the PFLP </F>
by unidentified reporter; place and date not given] 
  [Text] [AL-BILAD] What are the obvious lessons to be 
learned from the grisly Hebron massacre? 
  [Habash] The massacre takes us back to the heart of the 
Zionist agenda and its objectives. If there is a lesson to be 
learned from the atrocity, this must be to put the Zionist game 
plan under the magnifying glass, particularly at this moment 
when numerous forces, including Zionism, imperialism, and 
defeatist Arab forces are trying to cover up the true nature of 
the Zionist agenda. Accordingly, it is imperative for 
Palestinian and Arab masses to define their pan-Arab agenda and 
aim at weeding out that cancerous growth. 
  [AL-BILAD] What will the PFLP's [Popular Front for the 
Liberation of Palestine] response to the incident be? Are you 
planning any action? 
  [Habash] Naturally, all our comrades in the occupied 
territories must think up tangible reactions. Palestinian and 
Arab masses outside Palestine must also translate their 
condemnation of the massacre into action. I do not want to 
offer the military struggle as an alterative to the intifadah or 
mass and political struggle. What is called for is an 
integrated militlary, political, and popular plan of action. 

</TEXT>

