<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   PFLP-GC: `Military Operations' To Target Settlers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0103152494 Amman AL-BILAD in Arabic 2 Mar 94 p 6 </F>
<F P=103> JN0103152494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-BILAD </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ahmad Jibril, secretary general of the Popular Front 
for the Liberation of Palestine-General Command [PFLP-GC] has 
said in an exclusive interview with AL-BILAD that the Zionist 
enemy's atrocious and terrorist campaigns are nothing new. The 
massacre at the Ibrahimi Mosque committed at dawn last Friday 
will not be the last, he addded. 
  He said that this brutal massacre came naturally to the 
Israeli enemy, that it is part of common practices against our 
people in Palestine--a people who will not be terrorized by all 
the practices of occupation or by any Israeli military power. 
Their determination to liberate their occupied homeland will 
not be harmed, he added. 
  He said: The brutal massacre the Zionist enemy committed 
against worshipers in the mosque reflects the concessions [made 
by Yasir 'Arafat], which ignore the Palestinian's blood, 
dignity, and rights. The massacre is the fruit of the 
Gaza-Jericho agreement, which has made the Zionist enemy's path 
shorter and given legitimacy to its occupation. 
  He added that what the Ibrahimi Mosque witnessed makes us 
see 
that the real killers are those who encouraged the Jews--such as 
'Arafat--and extended their hands, which are stained with the 
bloods of the people and the cause, to shake the hand of the 
enemy. This enemy found that its interest are served by the 
concessions offered by the 'Arafat leadership. 
  Meanwhile, 'Abd-al-Jabir Burghul, member of the PFLP-GC 
Central Committee told AL-BILAD: We in the PFLP-GC were not at 
all surprised by the massacres committed by the gangs of 
settlers in the occupied territories. Before these massacres, 
several massacres were committed by [Former Israeli Prime 
Minister Menachem] Begin and other Zionist gangs such as the 
massacres in Dayr Yasin, Qibyah, Nahhalin, and Sabra and 
Shatila. The history of the Zionist movement is full of 
massacres against the Palestinian people. 
  He said: We in the PFLP-GC will never halt our Palestinian 
armed struggle in the occupied territories. The coming days 
will witness military operations against this entity in the 
occupied territories, not outside. 
  He said these operations will target the settlers and the 
gangs that supervised the execution of these massacres, in 
addition to assassinating Israeli officials in the Zionist camps 
as happened in the operation of Khalid Akar [not further 
identified]. 
  He expressed the belief that 'Arafat will go ahead in the 
negotiations process, and said: 'Arafat is a man who became 
involved in this process and will not retreat, the same thing 
happened with [Former Egyptian President Anwar] al-Sadat. We 
hope that what is taking place in the occupied territories will 
be a lesson to 'Arafat and his clique, and that they will 
benefit from this lesson and refrain from wagering on the 
Zionist enemy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-12484 </DOCNO>
