<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Speaker Birri Says Israel Seeks `War, Not Peace' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0203104794 Beirut Voice of Lebanon in Arabic 1015 GMT 2 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0203104794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Voice of Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Chamber of Deputies Speaker Nabih Birri has said all 
the signs mean that Israel is seeking war, not peace. He added 
that Israel is behind the Sayyidat al-Najat Church explosion in 
Zuq and emphasized that the al-Ibrahimi Msoque massacre in 
Hebron is against the region's peace process. 
  He noted that the Arabs are facing real terrorism and that 
peace cannot be achieved unilaterally. He said the bloodshed in 
Palestine and south Lebanon proves Israel's failure to make 
peace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

