<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hizballah Deputy Leader Comments on Massacres </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0203080994 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 0530 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0203080994 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Commenting on the recent massacres, Hizballah Deputy 
Secretary General Shaykh Na'im Qasim stated that political and 
human massacres cannot serve as a means to put out our nation's 
torch and weaken the nation's efforts for liberation. He said: 
If they imagine that massacres will scare us and make the 
nation retreat, they are mistaken. 
  Addressing a ceremony marking the anniversary of the birth 
of 
Imam al-Husayn and the Badr battle yesterday, Shaykh Qasim said: 
We are not only facing a plan to occupy the land of Palestine, 
but a plan to occupy the whole region. The West and its 
followers who claim to be Palestinian political leaders are 
working to take the land from its owners and perpetuate the 
usurping Israeli entity in the region. 
  He affirmed that the only response to the Israeli-U.S. plan 
is to continue the resistance so that the West and Israel will 
be unable to commit massacres in our region. 

</TEXT>

