<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Knesset Committee Briefed on Hebron Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0103124094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1200 GMT 1 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0103124094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Major General Dani Yatom, commander of the IDF 
[Israel Defense Forces] Central Command, told the Knesset 
Foreign Affairs and Defense Committee today that the debriefing 
conducted by the IDF among the wounded and the families of the 
victims of the Cave of the Patriarchs massacre indicates that 30 
worshipers were killed by the shots fired by Dr. Barukh 
Goldstein in the cave itself, four Palestinians were killed near 
the al-Ahali hospital, and another man was killed in a 
neighborhood near the Cave of the Patriarchs. Our correspondent 
Yo'el Nir reports that according to Gen. Yatom, these figures 
are not final but are based on the information available as of 
last night. The number of people wounded is still being 
examined. Gen. Yatom added that he has worked out new 
procedures governing prayer in the Cave of the Patriarchs but 
has not submitted them to the political echelon yet. 
  Chief of Staff Ehud Baraq told the committee that the 
newspapers published a list of names of 47 people killed in the 
massacre. An examination of this list, however, showed that 
several of the persons on it are still alive and that some were 
only wounded. The list also includes some inaccurate names. 
The chief of staff believes this is the reason for the gap 
between the various calculations. 

</TEXT>

