<H3> <TI>   Gur: Hebron Took `Defense Establishment' by Surprise </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0203142294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 2 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0203142294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Defense Minister Mordekhay Gur has said that 
no one in the defense establishment had anticipated that a man 
would get up and do what the murderer Goldstein did. We were 
taken by surprise, the deputy minister admitted. Our 
correspondent Hayim Hecht reports that, speaking before the 
Knesset plenum, Deputy Minister Gur said that very harsh steps 
will be taken against the supporters of Kakh. At the same time, 
however, the administration will attempt to avoid discrediting 
all of the Jewish settlers in the territories. 
  Our correspondent reports that the Knesset debate was very 
stormy. Knesset Members [MK's] 'Abd-al-Wahhab Darawshah and 
Rehav'am Ze'evi called each other terrorist and murderer, and 
other MK's rushed to separate the two rivals. 
  Deputy Minister Gur pleaded with the Arab MK's to go back 
on, 
and refrain from making statements linking the IDF [Israel 
Defense Forces] with Barukh Goldstein's shooting. Such claims 
are blood libel, Gur said. 

</TEXT>

