<H3> <TI>   Rabin's Office Denies Complaint About Goldstein </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0203075094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 28 
Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0203075094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It has been stated by Prime Minister Rabin's office 
that no telegram was received by the office from the head of the 
Supreme Muslim Council in Jerusalem and the head of the Waqf in 
Hebron containing a complaint about Barukh Goldstein, the Hebron 
murderer. 
  Meretz Knesset member 'Anat Ma'or today presented the 
telegram in which the two complain that more than four months 
ago Goldstein attacked the muezzin in the mosque in the Cave of 
the Patriarchs and tried to damage the carpets in this mosque. 

