<H3> <TI>   Police Capture 4 `Terrorists' in Gaza Strip </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0103193594 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1800 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0103193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1800 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A Border Police patrol captured four armed 
terrorists in Khan Yunus in the southern part of the Gaza Strip 
this afternoon. Our army affairs correspondent Alon Ben-David 
reports that the terrorists were carrying two submachine guns 
and three revolvers. Rioting continued throughout the Gaza Strip 
today, especially in the southern part of the Strip. Youths 
clashed with IDF [Israel Defense Forces] soldiers in Khan Yunus 
and Rafah. Nine residents were lightly injured. Eighteen 
firebombs were hurled at IDF troops in the Gaza Strip today. 
There were no casualties. Ten explosive charges were also 
discovered and safely dismantled. Gaza City and the nearby 
refugee camps remain under curfew. The IDF has up till now 
refrained from clamping a curfew on the southern part of the 
Gaza Strip despite the disturbances which have continued since 
last Friday [25 February]. 

</TEXT>

