<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres Undergoes Surgery Over Weekend </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA2702143694 Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT in Hebrew 27 Feb 94 p 
28 </F>

<F P=103> TA2702143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv YEDI'OT AHARONOT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by political correspondent Shim'on Schiffer] </F>
  [Text] Over the weekend, Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres 
underwent surgery somewhere around the eye area. 
  His doctors obliged him to wear an eye patch to cover the 
treated area. Consequently, Peres decided not to appear in 
public. 
  Peres did not participate in the cabinet session on Friday 
[25 February] nor in the meeting Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin 
held yesterday with the heads of the diplomatic corps in Israel. 
  The foreign minister is working from his home in Jerusalem 
and even granted an interview to Qol Yisra'el. It has been 
learned from his office that he will return to work within the 
next few days. 

</TEXT>

