<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Technical Problem' Prevents Launching of Arrow Missile </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0103143294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1300 GMT 1 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0103143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A test launching of the Arrow missile took place 
this morning. The target missile was fired at approximately 
1100 [0900 GMT] but during the countdown, there was a 
malfunctioning in the ground system which prevented the 
launching of the intercepting missile. 
  Our army affairs correspondent Karmela Menashe reports that 
the technical problem had nothing to with either the target or 
intercepting missiles. The date of the next launching will be 
decided after the reason for the problem is located. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

