<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Comments on Hebron, Other Issues </TI></H3>
<H4>   Calls Downing of Serb Planes `Good' </H4>
<F P=102> NC0103151094 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1441 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0103151094 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Mar (MENA)--Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa has 
stated that the shooting down of four Serb aircraft by NATO jet 
fighters is proof of NATO's seriousness in carrying out its 
ultimatum addressed to Serbia within the framework of UN 
resolutions. In a statement today, he said that this action was 
supposed to have been done earlier, but is still good 
nonetheless. He said that according to the reports we have 
received, the resolution on moving heavy weapons 20 km from 
Sarajevo has been violated. He stressed the need to strike at 
the forces that violate this resolution. 

</TEXT>

