<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Source' Denies Student Demonstrators Fired Upon </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0103161594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1512 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0103161594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 1 Mar (MENA)-- A responsible security source 
has denied that any security man has fired a single bullet at 
the students who staged demonstrations in universities in 
protest over the Ibrahimi Mosque massacre. In a statement 
today, he said that the security men's task was to prevent the 
students from leaving the university campus to preserve security 
and stability. He stressed that reports that certain security 
men fired bullets at students are totally baseless and false. 
He asserted that the task of the security men is primarily to 
keep law and order and maintain stability, noting that students 
have the right to express their feelings by staging a peaceful 
demonstration inside the campus without causing riots and 
instability. 

</TEXT>

