<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armed Islamic Group Head, 9 Colleagues, Killed 26 Feb </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2702154194 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 1500 
GMT 27 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD2702154194 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] It was learned today from the security services that 
Mourad Sid Ahmed, alias Djaafar El Afghani, the leader of the 
Armed Islamic Group [GIA] and nine members of his group were 
liquidated yesterday in the Algiers heights. The name of Djaafar 
El Afghani was linked to the kidnapping of three French citizens 
on 24 October 1993 outside their home in Krim Belkacem street. 
They were Mr. and Mrs. Tivano and Mr. Allan. The second case 
in which Djaafar El Afghani was implicated was the kidnapping of 
Cheikh Mohamed Bouslimani, the chairman of the Irshad and Islah 
[Guidance and Reform] charity society from his home in Blida 
last November. 

</TEXT>

