<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy Urges Security Council To Protect Palestinians </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0103135794 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1200 GMT 1 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0103135794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Fu'ad al-Batayinah, charge d'affaires of the 
Jordanian mission at the United Nations, has called on the 
Security Council to embark on measures to protect the 
Palestinians under occupation in accordance with the Security 
Council resolutions on the illegitimacy of Israeli settlements. 
Addressing the Security Council during its session last night 
to discuss the massacre at the holy Ibrahimi Mosque, 
al-Batayinah said: What is required is to provide effective 
protection for the Palestinian people to ensure their safety, 
security, and basic liberties, to save the holy places from 
desecration, and to remove the Israeli settlements. The 
objective, he added, is to continue the peace process to reach a 
just and honorable settlement based on Israeli withdrawal from 
all occupied Arab territory and to ensure the Palestinian 
people's legitimate rights. 

</TEXT>

