<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Comments on Hebron, Other Issues </TI></H3>
<H4>   Urges Disarming Hebron Settlers </H4>
<F P=102> NC0103150894 Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network in 
Arabic 1400 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0103150894 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo Arab Republic of Egypt Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister 'Amr Musa emphasized today that the 
situation in the occupied Arab territories remains dangerous and 
demanded that matters be brought under control in line with 
international law and in accordance with Israel's responsibility 
as an occupying power. 
  The foreign minister said that consultations are under way 
at 
the UN Security Council to issue a resolution about the Hebron 
massacre. He noted the need to prevent a recurrence of such a 
hideous incident by disarming the settlers in the Hebron area. 
  He added: If the settlers are going to have weapons for 
self-defense, the Palestinians must be given the same right. If 
the occupying power protects both the settlers and the 
Palestinians, this will be another matter and in that case the 
settlers' weapons must be removed. 
  Musa said such a measure would serve the interests of the 
Israelis and the Palestinians. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

