<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Well-Informed' Sources Comment on Bombing Investigation </TI></H3>
<H4>   Socialist Party Condemns Bombing </H4>
<F P=102> NC0203080294 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 0530 
GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0203080294 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In response to the Church massacre, the Progressive 
Socialist Party has asked international organizations to 
reconsider the acquittal of Zionism and confront Israeli 
barbarism and racism. 
  The party's Foreign Relations Office has cabled the United 
Nations secretary general, the Arab League secretary general, 
Amnesty International, the EU president, the secretary general 
of the Islamic countries organization, his holiness the pope, 
and the president of Socialist International. 
  The cable said: We cabled you a few days ago condemning the 
Zionists' horrendous massacre at the al-Ibrahimi Mosque in 
Hebron. Today, we cable you to condemn another massacre 
perpetrated by the same hand against innocent worshipers in 
Sayyidat al-Najat Church in Zuq, Lebanon. These and many 
previous massacres confirm the nature of Zionism and require us 
all to reconsider some UN resolutions that acquitted Zionism and 
(?overlooked) its past and present. We urge international and 
regional institutions, all human rights organizations, and all 
countries and parties to adopt immediate, courageous positions 
against this barbaric racism, which denies every human right and 
threatens world peace if its interests are not served. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

