<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Well-Informed' Sources Comment on Bombing Investigation </TI></H3>
<H4>   Iranian Embassy Condemns Bombing </H4>
<F P=102> LD0103152894 Tehran IRNA in English 1302 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD0103152894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beirut, March 1, IRNA -- Iran's embassy in a 
statement issued here Monday strongly condemned the Sunday 
explosion of a bomb in a Maronite church in Juniyah port in 
Lebanon. 
  Explosion of the church was a criminal act with the 
objective 
to cover the massacre of Muslim Palestinians in Hebron, the 
statement read. 
  The embassy's statement which was quoted in Tuesday's papers 
here, stressed that "the hand which shed the Muslims blood in 
Hebron, was the same which exploded the Maronite church." At 
the end of the statement, the embassy expressed sympathy with 
the victims families as well as the Christian Lebanese community. 
  Ten people were killed and 60 injured on Sunday due to the 
explosion of a bomb at the altar of the Maronite church in 
Juniyah port. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

