<H3> <TI>   General Strike Observed To Protest Hebron Killings </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0303105094 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0900 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0303105094 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] A general strike is being observed in all Lebanese 
areas today to mark the first week since the Ibrahimi Mosque 
massacre in Hebron in which 43 Palestinians were killed and 
hundreds were wounded. 
  Studies have stopped in schools and universities. Banks, 
government departments, and shops have closed their doors. 
Traffic on the streets is light. The strike covers areas under 
the Israeli occupation in the south and western al-Biqa'. 

</TEXT>

