<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Progressive Socialists, Communists Condemn Hebron Event </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC2502135394 Shanayh Voice of the Mountain in Arabic 1230 
GMT 25 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC2502135394 </F>
<F P=104>  Shanayh Voice of the Mountain </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Following the horrible massacre, the Progressive 
Socialist Party [PSP] Foreign Relations Office sent cables to 
the UN secretary general, Arab League secretary general, Amnesty 
International, the EU president, the secretary general of the 
Islamic Countries League [as heard], the pope, and the head of 
Socialist International. 
  The cables said in part: The horrendous massacre that the 
Zionists committed today against innocent Palestinian 
worshippers is the greatest evidence of terrorism and delinquent 
behavior demonstrated by the usurping Israeli entity since it 
was founded with the help of those who claim to be concerned 
about civilization, democracy, freedom, and human rights. 
  If this is the promised Israeli peace, then let it be seen 
by 
the entire world's international, regional, and humanitarian 
institutions. We and history await your stance and your verdict. 
  The Lebanese Communist Party [LCP] denounced the massacre 
and 
said it was an attempt to impose additional conditions on the 
Palestinian side and put pressure on other Arab parties. 

</TEXT>

