<F P=100> ARABIAN PENINSULA </F>
<F P=101> Yemen </F>
<H3> <TI>   Military Committee Visits Commands in Abyan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2802211094 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
2000 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2802211094 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The military committee, composed of a Yemeni 
military team, a Jordanian military team, an Omani military 
team, and the U.S. and French military attaches, this afternoon 
began to pay field visits to Abyan Governorate. 
  After arriving in Abyan Governorate, the committee visited 
the Madram Brigade Command and explained the measures taken and 
the decisions that the committee has made in accordance with the 
powers authorized by the political leadership. 
  Afterward, the committee visited the al-'Amaliqah Brigade 
Command and explained the measures agreed by the joint military 
committee as well as the tasks that will be carried out through 
direct supervision and monitoring in order to make sure that the 
forces have returned to their previous positions and that the 
checkpoints and recently erected roadblocks have been removed. 
  The joint committee has set up a field subcommittee from its 
personnel. The subcommittee is charged with staying in Abyan in 
order to follow up the implementation of instructions and make 
sure that all parties comply with them. 
  The committee voiced satisfaction with the commitment to the 
instructions, issued by both the defense minister and the chief 
of staff, to all units to return to their positions in 
accordance with the directives of the political leadership. 

</TEXT>

