<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Peres States Willingness To Discuss PLO Requests </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0203194594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1900 GMT 2 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0203194594 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres said this evening 
that Israel will agree to discuss new PLO requests, provided 
they do not contradict the Declaration of Principles [DOP]. 
Speaking at a conference on Jewish communications in Jerusalem, 
Peres noted that the deputy Russian foreign minister and the 
Greek foreign minister, arrived in Israel today from Tunis. 
They brought a message from the PLO leadership stating it is 
very important that Israel realize these are indeed conditions 
for the resumption of the negotiations. 
  Minister Peres clarified that Israel had accepted some of 
the 
conditions, including the release of prisoners. Israel agrees 
that the UN Security Council resolution on the Hebron massacre 
include a temporary placement of foreign presence in Jericho and 
Gaza, in accordance with the DOP. We are also willing to 
discuss the Palestinian request that the autonomy police force 
be larger, Peres said. Our correspondent Amy Rhodes filed this 
report. 

</TEXT>

