<H3> <TI>   Telecommunication Workers Cut Telephone Lines </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0303131794 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1200 GMT 3 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0303131794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The District Labor Court in Tel Aviv is due to begin 
considering a request by the Bezeq [Telecommunications Company] 
management to issue a restraining order against workers who have 
adopted measures that have caused serious interruptions in 
telephone communications all over the country. Our 
correspondent Meron Tzur reports that the workers have 
deliberately cut telephone communications to hundreds of 
thousands of subscribers. 
  Dozens of company workers stormed the office of the director 
general of the Telecommunications Ministry in Megdal Shalom in 
Tel Aviv at noon today, shouting loudly to prevent him from 
explaining the nature of the Bezeq Company's new license. 

</TEXT>

