<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Envoy: Israel Reponsible for `Regional Extremism' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0303144794 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1215 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0303144794 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] New York -- Syria has stressed that the horrendous 
Hebron massacre falls within the framework of the Israeli 
occupation and settlement policy, which is in violation of all 
laws and UN resolutions. 
  Addressing the Security Council last night, Syrian UN 
Representative Husayn 'Awwad said Israel's intransigent attitude 
and expansionist policies, which have persisted since the start 
of the Middle East peace talks in Madrid in 1991, are either 
directly or indirectly responsible for regional extremism. He 
added that Israel has been playing a dual game since the start 
of the Middle East peace process and that the Hebron massacre is 
part of an organized and planned operation, not an individual 
act as asserted by Israel. The government of Israel bears 
responsibility for this massacre, he added. 
  'Awwad said that unless the United States and Russia, the 
cosponsors of the peace process, intervene for the sake of 
reaching a just, lasting, and comprehensive solution in the 
Middle East, Israel will then implement Yitzhaq Shamir's 
slogans, which he summed up in the following phrase: Negotiate 
with the Arabs for years, but do not allow these talks to 
produce any results. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

