<H3> <TI>   Hebron-Born Resident Stabs Jordanian Doctor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0303090594 Amman AL-DUSTUR in Arabic 3 Mar 94 pp 36, 30 </F>
<F P=103> JN0303090594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-DUSTUR </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] (A.S.), a 24-year old originally from Hebron and a 
resident of Amman, has stabbed Dr. 'Umar al-Far, who works in a 
private clinic, and his wife Olga, who is a Russian national and 
works as a nurse at Malhas Hospital, with a knife while they 
were downtown near the Habiba sweets shop near a shoe store. 
  The doctor was injured in the chest while his wife suffered 
wounds to the back. A youth who works inside the shoe store 
tried to intervene and was also injured. All are reported to be 
in good condition. Police arrested the assailant. 

</TEXT>

