<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Omani Envoy Conveys Message on Situation in Yemen </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN2402074394 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 0500 GMT 
24 Feb 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN2402074394 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty King Husayn received Yusuf Bin-'Alawi 
'Abdallah, Omani minister of state for foreign affairs, at the 
Royal Hashemite Court last night. The minister conveyed to his 
majesty a verbal message from his brother His Majesty Sultan 
Qabus Bin-Sa'id of Oman dealing with Jordanian-Omani efforts and 
coordination to bring the views of the various Yemeni parties 
closer, especially after the success of Jordanian efforts that 
culminated in the signing of the Yemeni document of pledge and 
accord, which safeguards the unity of sisterly Yemen and helps 
build its modern state. 
  The talks also dealt with the distinguished relations 
between 
the two sisterly countries as well as regional and international 
issues of common concern. 
  His Majesty King Husayn asked the guest minister to convey 
his greetings to his brother His Majesty Sultan Qabus Bin-Sa'id. 
  Dr. 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali, the prime minister; His 
Excellency al-Sharif Zayd Bin-Shakir, chief of the Royal 
Hashemite Court; Marwan al-Qasim, his majesty's political 
adviser; Talal Sat'an al-Hasan, minister of state for foreign 
affairs; and the Omani ambassador in Amman attended the audience. 
  Bin-'Alawi arrived in Amman yesterday evening and was 
received upon arrival by Marwan al-Qasim and Talal Sat'an 
al-Hasan. 

</TEXT>

