<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mubarak Reiterates Condemnation of Mosque Massacre </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0203142294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1300 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC0203142294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Cairo, 2 Mar (MENA)--President Husni Mubarak has 
reiterated Egypt's denunciation of the massacre at the Ibrahimi 
Mosque in Hebron, which he described as the epitome of cruelty 
and extremism. President Mubarak noted that he is following up 
the situation and the contacts held with U.S. President Bill 
Clinton, Palestinian president Yasir 'Arafat, and the Israeli 
president and prime minister. 
  During an expanded meeting held at the presidential office 
today, President Mubarak stressed that Egypt urges the 
international community to adopt a clear-cut decision to back 
the Palestinian people's right to protection under international 
law, disarm the settlers, and take an interest in the security 
requirements of the Palestinian people to ensure the security 
and safety of Palestinian civilians. 
  Following the three-hour meeting, Information Minister 
Safwat 
al-Sharif stated that its purpose was to discuss domestic 
affairs on which the president gave instructions at an earlier 
meeting. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

