<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Mufti Urges Killing of Israelis </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0203135294 Cairo AL-'ARABI in Arabic 28 Feb 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> NC0203135294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-'ARABI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] His Eminence Mufti of the Republic Dr. Muhammad 
Sayyid Tantawi has called on Palestinians to kill an equal 
number of Israelis. Asked by an AL-'ARABI correspondent if an 
earlier statement he made, expressing readiness for dialogue 
with the Israelis, remains valid after the massacre in the 
Ibrahimi mosque, the mufti asked: "What is the use of canceling 
dialogue between the Arabs and Israelis?" 
  The AL-'ARABI correspondent said the mufti's office 
represents a symbol for Muslims in Egypt and is therefore in a 
delicate position; it must not get embroiled in efforts aimed at 
normalization with the enemy, something that several 
professional associations and popular organizations still 
oppose. The mufti commented, saying: "Don't get emotional. We 
are averse to dialogue with no one, as long as it can help to 
solve problems and conflicts." 

</TEXT>

