<H3> <TI>   IRNA Chief Urges Exposing Israeli Crimes </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD2802225894 Tehran IRNA in English 2240 GMT 28 Feb 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2802225894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, Feb. 28, IRNA -- Managing Director of the 
Islamic Republic News Agency (IRNA) and Chairman of the 
Non-aligned News Agencies Pool (NANAP), Fereydun Verdinezhad on 
Monday sent messages to chiefs of NANAP member news agencies, on 
last Friday's massacre of Palestinian worshippers in al-Khalil 
mosque, and urged them to reveal the nature of the latest 
Israeli crime to the world. 
  He regretted that although crimes of racist nature such as 
those in Bosnia-Herzegovina and the lates one in occupied 
Palestine, have increased of late, "the horrifying aspects of 
the crimes are treated lightly by world news agencies." 
  Verdinejad expressed hope that nanap members, bearing in 
mind 
the principle of free-thinking of the non-aligned movement and 
their own professional responsibilities would do their best to 
convey the message of the long-suffering people to the world and 
expose the criminals. 
  The message emphasized that the murder and the massacre of 
civilians by the military, in the name of human rights and 
freedom, should be stopped as soon as possible. 
  More than 60 fasting Muslims were gunned down in cold blood 
at the Prophet Ibrahim mosque in al-Khalil by Zionist agents 
last Friday. 

</TEXT>

