<F P=100> Iran </F>
<H3> <TI>   Commentary Views 'Arafat's `Conciliatory Approach' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  LD0203141694 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 1101 GMT 2 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD0203141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Station commentary] </F>
  [Excerpts] Five days after the bloody tragedy of Ibrahim 
mosque in Hebron, during which more than 600 innocent 
Palestinians were either killed or wounded, the PLO Chairman 
Yasir 'Arafat at last decided to call off talks with the Zionist 
regime for the time being. Shortly after this bloody tragedy, 
U.S. President Clinton invited 'Arafat to Washington to hold 
talks with the Zionist regime led by Prime Minister Yitzhaq 
Rabin on ways of solving implementation problems of the 
Gaza-Jericho accord. 'Arafat hastily accepted this invitation. 
However, the united and angry response of the Palestine people 
in the face of the Zionist regime's horrific crime and its 
repercussions in the entire Arab and Islamic world pushed 
'Arafat into a corner and he excused himself. [passage omitted] 
  It is quite natural that under the existing explosive 
situation in Palestinian society no one dares hold talks with 
the Zionist regime under the name of the Palestinian people. 
'Arafat's decision to call off the talks at this stage is in 
fact a message to those responsible for the massacre of the 
innocent people that they should not worry as the talks will 
resume as soon as the circumstances change and the Palestinians 
calm down. Whereas the Palestinians in the occupied territories 
and the people of neighboring countries including Egypt, Jordan, 
and Lebanon have staged rallies and protest marches to demand 
the ultimate cancellation of the talks. No doubt the adoption 
of a conciliatory approach on the talks with the Zionist regime 
-- at a time when there are clear signs that the Zionist regime 
was directly involved in the massacre of the worshippers in the 
Ibrahim mosque -- is a step to win the support of the Zionist 
regime and the White House statesmen. Such an approach 
definitely seeks to serve the interests of the Zionist regime 
and the White House. The Palestinians demand something 
different and have announced this demand explicitly. 

</TEXT>

