<H3> <TI>   Joint Iranian-Pakistani Naval Maneuvers End 2 Mar </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  NC0303061194 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0430 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC0303061194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Persian </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The joint naval maneuvers of the Islamic Republic of 
Iran and Pakistan in the northern water of the Indian Ocean 
ended last night. 
  The Central News Unit reports from Islamabad that in the 
last 
phase of these maneuvers, defense operations against air threats 
and attacks on amphibian and submarine units were carried out. 
The participating units displayed the most modern tactics in 
these exercises. 
  The four-phase maneuvers included four warships, several 
naval reconnaissance planes, and antisubmarine helicopters of 
the Iranian Navy as well as five warships, one submarine, and 
several planes and helicopters from the Pakistani Air Force. 
  The plans for the joint maneuvers were drawn up by the 
Iranian Navy and the Pakistani Navy undertook the executive 
management. 

</TEXT>

