<F P=103> JN0203175294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Deputy Prime Minister Tariq 'Aziz has called for 
efforts to be intensified and for objections to be more loudly 
raised in the region and the world against the unjust ones and 
aggressors who covet peoples' rights and threaten their security 
and legitimate interests. He stressed the need for justice and 
peace to prevail among peoples. 
  Receiving a delegation of Eastern Catholic patriarchs, Tariq 
'Aziz reviewed the dimensions of the plot that targets all 
countries of the region and their peoples' security, stability, 
and peace. He said that the unjust blockade, which the arrogant 
powers, especially the United States and Zionism, insist on 
imposing on Iraq, constitutes one of the landmarks of this plot. 
He stressed that the blockade must be lifted since Iraq has 
honored its obligations in accordance with Resolution 687. 
  Bishop Rafael (Bidawid), head of the delegation and the 
Babylon Chaldean patriarchate, stressed the need to put an end 
to the suffering of the patient Iraqi people through serious 
[word indistinct] at all forums to lift the unjust blockade and 
to establish peace and justice in the region. 

