<F P=100> IRAQ </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Mine Explodes, Kills 3 Children in Safwan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0303104394 Baghdad INA in Arabic 0940 GMT 3 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0303104394 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Al-Basrah, southern Iraq, 3 Mar (INA)--Three 
children have been killed in the Safwan subdistrict when a mine 
dropped on farms there by U.S. aircraft during the hateful 
30-state aggression went off. 
  The newspaper AL-THAWRAH, quoting its correspondent in 
al-Basrah, said that when it went off, the mine killed two 
children instantly, tearing their bodies apart. As for the 
third child, he first lost his four limbs. He later died on his 
way to hospital. 
  The paper indicated that this incident is the third in the 
past two weeks. All in all, these incidents have killed six 
children and wounded 10 others in Safwan and nearby farms. 

</TEXT>

