<H3> <TI>   U.S. Aircraft Violations Protested to UN </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0103133894 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1100 GMT 1 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN0103133894 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] New York, 1 Mar (INA) -- Iraq has protested to the 
UN General Secretariat continuing U.S. aircraft violations of 
Iraq's airspace with the aim of provocation and surveillance, as 
well as dropping thermal flares. 
  In a memorandum he handed to UN Secretary General 
Butrus-Ghali, Iraq's permanent representative to the world body 
said that from 11 to 20 February, the aircraft mounted 569 
sorties over a wide area of northern and southern Iraq. 
  On 14 February, a hostile plane dropped four thermal flares 
over al-Badriyah of al-Qush sub-district in Ninawa Governorate. 
On 18 February, a hostile formation dropped two thermal flares 
over al-Namrud sub-district in Ninawa. On the same day, a 
hostile plane dropped three thermal flares north of the hamlet 
of Fa'idah in Ninawa Governorate. 
  Three U.S. TR-1 reconnaissance planes violated Iraq's 
airspace over al-Basrah, Qal'at Salih, al-'Amarah, al-Qurnah, 
Artawiyah, and Gharb al-Basiyah, and then headed to Saudi space. 

</TEXT>

