Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 2 Mar (INA)--Oil Minister Dr. Safa' Jawad 
Hadi today inaugurated the automatic al-Wa'iliyah liquid gas 
filling plant in Mosul, northern Iraq, on the occasion of the 
21st anniversary of the immortal nationalization anniversary, 
which was observed yesterday. The plant is the first automatic 
plant built by national Iraqi cadres. It has a production 
capacity of 15,000 gas cylinders per day in two shifts. 
  The expenses of the project amounted to 4 million dinars. No 
imported materials were used in the project. 

