<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Talks Said Stuck in `Vicious Circle,' Could Collapse </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PM2402100594 London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT in Arabic 23 Feb 94 p 5 </F>
<F P=103> PM2402100594 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Salwa al-Ustuwani: "Syria: Negotiations Going </F>
Round in Vicious Circle; Israel Continues To Exercise Evasion 
Method"] 
  [Excerpt] Damascus -- Syria said yesterday that Israel 
continues to use evasion as a method and is trying to perpetuate 
the explosive situation in the occupied Arab territories and to 
create a state of tension and instability in the region. 
  A Syrian official told AL-SHARQ AL-AWSAT that the Washington 
negotiations are still going round in a vicious circle and that 
the Israeli delegation continues to evade adherence to the peace 
process, first and foremost the full withdrawal from the Golan 
Heights and the other occupied territories. The official added 
that the Washington negotiations have considerably and clearly 
exposed Israel's hostile position toward the peace process. 
"The Israelis continue to raise the same issues and provoke the 
same obstacle with a view to prolonging the negotiations and 
using the wasted time to circumvent the results of the Geneva 
summit, get around the Security Council resolutions, and empty 
them of any substance." 
  The official went on to say that Rabin continues to insist 
on 
the tone of secret negotiations at a high level with the aim of 
torpedoing the negotiations and the U.S. initiative, eclipsing 
the resolutions of international legitimacy, and practicing 
blackmail against Syria, Lebanon, and the Arabs. Plus, Israel 
is going to impose other impossible conditions for the sake of 
playing for time and using the coming years in the service of 
its settlement schemes. 
  The official called on the United States to adopt a firm 
position so that the time will not be wasted, because Syria 
cannot continue to engage in futile negotiations forever or 
allow Israel to lie to world public opinion and say that it is 
continuing the peace process merely to achieve its expansionist 
schemes. 
  The official added that the peace process could collapse if 
Israel continues to ignore Arab demands. And Israel must know 
that there can be no peace in the region without Syria and that 
no agreement concluded with Israel has any hope of continuing or 
being implemented without Syria. Syria has a known and fixed 
position, namely not to relinquish a single inch of its 
territory or the other Arab territories. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

