<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Details Terms for Resumption of Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  TA0203141294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1400 GMT 2 Mar 
94 </F>

<F P=103> TA0203141294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Hebrew </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Here is a report just in: Yasir 'Arafat has sent a 
message to Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin detailing the PLO terms 
for peace talks resumption. This was reported by Palestinian 
sources in Tunis. They said Sa'ib 'Urayqat traveled from 
Jerusalem to Tunis to deliver the message. The PLO terms are as 
follow: 
  -- Israel will disarm the settlers and permit international 
presence in the territories. 
  -- Israel will stop expropriating Arab lands in the 
territories and building new settlements. 
  -- Israel will restructure several settlements situated 
close 
to Palestinian population centers, such as Netzarim in the Gaza 
Strip, Qiryat Arba', and two settlements in the Jericho area. 
'Arafat suggests that the Netzarim residents should be 
relocated to another settlement in southern Strip, and that 
Palestinians should be allowed to purchase some of the evacuated 
lands. 

</TEXT>

