<H3> <TI>   Executive Committee Dissidents Note Peace Talks </TI></H3>
<H4>   Al-Surani: Settlement Option `Leads Nowhere' </H4>
<F P=102> NC0203163694 Cairo AL-'ARABI in Arabic 28 Feb 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> NC0203163694 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo AL-'ARABI </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Salah 'Azazi] </F>
  [Text] PLO Executive Committee Member Jamal al-Surani has 
said that the entire Palestinian people are calling for breaking 
off the negotiations with Israel. He held the United States 
responsible for the Zionist massacre in Hebron. There is no 
point continuing the negotiated settlement until the U.S. 
position becomes clear, he said. 
  Al-Surani assailed demands by Clinton and Warren Christopher 
that the two sides demonstrate self-restraint, as though 
Palestine was the aggressor against Israel. He said: I pray 
God to remove the scales from the eyes of those who imagine 
something good will come of the U.S. position. It is the United 
States that provides weapons, aid, and all forms of support for 
Israel. 
  Al-Surani said the settlement option leads nowhere with the 
racist usurpers who are embraced by the United States. He 
called for a prompt meeting by the Arab foreign ministers, or 
else the Arabs will be colluding against each other. An Arab 
summit to react to the massacre must be held, he said. 

</TEXT>

