<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Abu-Sharif Suggests U.S. Purchase Settlements </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  JN0203202294 Sanaa Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1800 GMT 2 
Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN0203202294 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Voice of Palestine </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Arabic </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brother Bassam Abu-Sharif [adviser to PLO Chairman 
'Arafat] has called for the removal of the Jewish settlements 
from the occupied territories and proposed that the United 
States finance their purchase for the Palestinians. He said: 
Following the Hebron massacre that claimed the lives of 53 
Palestinians, it is necessary to remove the Jerwish settlements 
from the occupied territories to bring about peace between the 
Palestinians and the Israelis. He stressed that the Hebron 
massacre provided an opportunity for a two-stage settlement, and 
said that the lesson that has been learned shows clearly the 
need for the Israeli Army to withdraw from the occupied 
territories in implementation of the UN resolutions. 
  Brother Bassam Abu-Sharif also said that U.S. President Bill 
Clinton's invitation to the Palestinians and the Israelis to 
hold serious negotiations in Washington gives an opportunity to 
President Clinton to prove to the Arab and Islamic world his 
interest in peace. Concluding, he said that it is Washington's 
duty to intervene, in its capacity as a partner in the peace 
process, to completely end the Israeli occupation and to finance 
the purchase of Jewish settlements in the occupied West Bank and 
Gaza Strip for the Palestinians. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

